-- Oi shareholders approve capital hike, Portugal Telecom appraisal
-- By Luciana Bruno
-- Thu Mar 27, 2014 10:21AM EDT
-- None



RIO DE JANEIRO, March 27 (Reuters) - Shareholders of Brazilian telecommunications company Grupo Oi SA <OIBR3.SA> on Thursday approved a capital increase needed to combine with Portugal Telecom SA SGPS <PTC.LS>.

In a vote that took place in Rio de Janeiro, where Oi is based, shareholders also approved an appraisal made by an investment bank of the value of assets of Portugal Telecom, a prerequisite for the planned combination of both companies.